                    },
                    "body": "Patch to fix chunked encoding",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=chriskl",
                        "name": "chriskl",
                        "displayName": "Chris Kings-Lynne",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-05-23T03:40:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-05-23T03:40:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32908",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "To be more accurate, this happens when:\n- mbstring is loaded\n- mbstring.func_overload & 2\n- mbstring.internal_encoding is a multibyte-encoding \n\nThis is pretty hard to reproduce for those who don't have that setup - but I've added some unit tests that catch this (given the right php.ini configuration) and will look into solving this. This is actually a bigger problem, and affects several other places in Zend_Http and Zend_Uri. It was solved for Zend_OpenId by implementing a dedicated strlen() wrapper (see Zend_OpenId::strlen()) \n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2009-07-24T08:41:43.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2009-07-24T08:41:43.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/32910",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Resolved in rev. 17041 along with another related issue in Http_Client.\n\nBTW thanks for the ftell() idea - that worked well although I reduced the number of calls. I used mb_internal_encoding everywhere else, just to avoid the consecutive if() calls. \n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=shahar",
                        "name": "shahar",
                        "displayName": "Shahar Evron",
